# Excalidraw Architecture

## State Management

- Custom state via actionManager — NOT Redux/Zustand/MobX
- State updates: `actionManager.executeAction(action, source?, value?)` only — `ActionManager` has no `dispatch()`; use registered `Action` objects and the manager API
- State type: AppState (packages/excalidraw/types.ts)

## Rendering

- Canvas 2D rendering — NOT React DOM for drawing
- Render pipeline: Scene → renderScene() → canvas context
- DO NOT use react-konva, fabric.js, pixi.js

## Dependencies

- No new npm packages without explicit approval
- Check packages/utils/ before adding external helpers

## How to verify

### State management

- Confirm custom state goes through `actionManager`, not Redux, Zustand, or MobX
- Confirm state updates go through `actionManager.executeAction(...)` only (in tests, `API.executeAction` delegates to the same manager)
- Confirm relevant state is typed with `AppState` from `packages/excalidraw/types.ts`

### Rendering

- Confirm drawing uses Canvas 2D, not React DOM
- Confirm the render pipeline is `Scene` → `renderScene()` → canvas context
- Search for `react-konva`, `fabric.js`, and `pixi.js` -> should find no use

### Dependencies

- Confirm any new npm dependency was added only with explicit approval
- Before relying on a new external helper, search `packages/utils/` for an existing equivalent
